🚨 Current Problems

Legacy Step Scaling Pattern: Configuration uses deprecated step_scaling block outside alarms, which can cause unpredictable scaling behavior.
Policy Conflicts: Both target_tracking and step_scaling are defined for CPU, creating conflicting autoscaling policies that AWS doesn't support.
Broken Scale-In Logic: RequestCountPerTarget can only scale OUT (when > 1000 requests) but never scales IN because there's no LessThanThreshold alarm. Once scaled out, services stay at high capacity permanently, wasting resources and increasing costs.
